# Docker Cheat Sheet (Important Commands with Examples)

---

# 1. Docker Version & Info

## Check Docker Version

```bash id="0xhz8m"
docker --version
```

---

## Detailed Docker Information

```bash id="szs08s"
docker info
```

---

# 2. Images Commands

## List Images

```bash id="ztbjlwm"
docker images
```

---

## Pull Image from Docker Hub

```bash id="yw9c6v"
docker pull nginx
```

Example:

```bash id="h7v0cm"
docker pull ubuntu
```

---

## Remove Image

```bash id="6nqjj8"
docker rmi image_name
```

Example:

```bash id="4evd3j"
docker rmi nginx
```

Force remove:

```bash id="r4f3mf"
docker rmi -f nginx
```

---

# 3. Container Commands

## Run Container

```bash id="kmjlwm"
docker run nginx
```

---

## Run in Background (Detached Mode)

```bash id="jz3yxr"
docker run -d nginx
```

---

## Run with Custom Name

```bash id="vrjlwm"
docker run --name mycontainer nginx
```

---

## Port Mapping

```bash id="6r1sdp"
docker run -d -p 8080:80 nginx
```

Meaning:

* Host Port = 8080
* Container Port = 80

---

## Interactive Terminal Mode

```bash id="30w2zx"
