# 12. Important Exam Commands

| Task                     | Command                   |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------- |
| Check running containers | `docker ps`               |
| Pull image               | `docker pull nginx`       |
| Run container            | `docker run nginx`        |
| Stop container           | `docker stop id`          |
| Remove container         | `docker rm id`            |
| Remove image             | `docker rmi nginx`        |
| Build image              | `docker build -t app .`   |
| View logs                | `docker logs id`          |
| Execute command          | `docker exec -it id bash` |
| Push image               | `docker push repo/image`  |

---

# 13. Important MCQ Points

* Docker uses **containerization**
* Containers are lightweight
* Dockerfile used to build images
* Docker Hub stores images
* `docker ps` → running containers
* `docker images` → available images
* `docker compose` manages multi-container apps
* `-d` means detached/background mode
* `-p` means port mapping
* `-it` means interactive terminal

